\begin_inset Caption Standard

\begin_layout Plain Layout
 The spiral wavelet is a product of wavelets along time, log-frequency, and octave index. Blue and green oscillations represent the real and imaginary parts. The red envelope represents the complex modulus. Partials of an hypothetical harmonic sound are marked as thick dots. 
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "fig:spiral-wavelets"

\end_inset

 
\end_layout

